Under the name ‘asparagi’ are included several herbs besides the one we know by that name, which is only one of a tribe called by naturalists ‘asphodeleaef To the same belong the onion, gai-lie, and others. This is why the word is usually in 1110 plural. (S. v. 82.) ‘Villica’ is the wife of his ‘ villicus,' or head gardener. See S. iii. 228: “culti villicus horti.''
